==English==
===Etymology===
Named after the English physicist [[w:James Prescott Joule|James Prescott Joule]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|joul}}, {{IPA|/dʒaʊl/}}, {{SAMPA|/dZaUl/}}
*:[[Rhymes:English:-aʊl|Rhymes: -aʊl]]

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''joule'''
# In the [[International System of Units]], the [[derived unit]] of [[energy]], [[work]] and [[heat]]; the work required to [[exert]] a [[force]] of one [[newton]] for a [[distance]] of one [[metre]]. Also equal to a power of one [[watt]] for a duration of one [[second]]. Symbol: [[J]]

